	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Dr Mario has two 32Kbyte ROMs. SEROM accepts 32K PRG maximum and 64K CHR maximum. That would be your limitations for it. I don't know if a 64kbyte eprom has the same pinout or not, maybe it does. The 32K eprom should be the same though.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/SxROM">http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/SxROM</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
